main event: A crescent-shaped UFO was observed in the sky, appearing brighter than the background stars, descending vertically, and moving from left to right below the horizon. No photographs were taken of the object.
interesting points: The UFO was described as crescent-shaped and appeared brighter than the surrounding stars.
It descended vertically and moved from left to right below the horizon.
No photographs were taken of the UFO despite the approximately 15-minute observation time.
The report suggests reactivating a visual/radar project to gather further information.
The UFO sighting was accompanied by handwritten notes and communications between military personnel and intelligence agencies.
location: Texas, 13 miles south of Duncanville AFS
witnesses: multiple witnesses, including military and intelligence personnel
